des-o-late  (dĕs'ɘ-lĭt, dĕz'-)
adj.

Devoid of inhabitants; deserted: “The malls which were once filled with many people have now grown desolate” 

Barren; lifeless: The cold, desolate ice caps of the South Poal.


Rendered unfit for habitation or use: the desolate sands of the Arabian desert.

Dreary; dismal.

Bereft of friends or hope; sad and forlorn. See Synonyms at sad.